HEADWORD: Puncto
<hw>Punc"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Punto</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A nice point of form or
ceremony.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A term applied to the point in fencing.</def>
<rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punctual</ent>⟦br⟧
